overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, which included database and API endpoints, against a detailed
  specification and Statement of Work. The review identified several critical
  gaps, including the absence of a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection,
  insufficient sleep syndrome detection, outbound resource links, and weighted
  EDS scoring. Following the review, the agent proceeded to implement these
  missing features. This involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI
  components for the questionnaire, and the logic for both the web-based and PDF
  reports to accurately reflect the new criteria and provide appropriate
  messaging and recommendations.
